FIX (1 line): In server.py ws_room(), add an explicit `await websocket.close(code=4008)` (or 4000) inside the `except (WebSocketDisconnect, asyncio.TimeoutError)` block (or simply in a try/except in the finally), so idle clients are actively kicked at the 10s deadline. Suggested patch:

    except (WebSocketDisconnect, asyncio.TimeoutError):
        try:
            await websocket.close(code=4008)
        except Exception:
            pass

This makes the test_no_join_message_disconnects_within_10s pass and prevents idle-WS resource leaks.
